    "deployment_risks": "Under real batch sizes (500), the unbounded concurrency will cause downstream saturation. This is a production-time-bomb, not a theoretical risk.",
    "rollback_capability": "Function is stateless; rollback is safe assuming processDelivery is idempotent.",
    "backward_compatibility": "Adding concurrency limiting is backward-compatible; no API change needed.",
    "monitoring_coverage": "No logging or metrics emitted — batch failures will be invisible unless the caller logs the result.",
    "breaking_changes": {
